description: By Yiannis Kourtoglou and Stamos Prousalis
title: Aid ship for Gaza expected to depart Cyprus this weekend

description: Argentina's monthly inflation reading likely slowed to 15.3% in February, still painfully high but down sharply from a peak in December, as new libertarian President Javier Milei's austerity drive squeezes shoppers, helping rein in grocery price rises.
title: Argentina inflation seen cooling as Milei austerity tempers food prices

description: Armenia is considering applying for European Union membership, foreign minister Ararat Mirzoyan said on Friday, as it seeks to forge closer ties with the West in the face of tensions with traditional ally Russia.
title: Armenia is considering seeking EU membership, foreign minister says

description: U.S. Secretary of State Antony Blinken spoke with Kenyan President William Ruto about the Haiti crisis and the two men underscored their commitment to a multinational security mission to restore order, the State Department said on Saturday.
title: Blinken talks to Kenyan president about Haiti crisis, says State Dept

description: Guy Philippe, who helped lead a coup in Haiti in 2004 and returned to the Caribbean island last year after serving a prison sentence in the U.S., demanded on Friday that the country's prime minister resign and said he wanted to become president.
title: Exclusive: Haiti ex-coup leader Guy Philippe demands PM resign, wants presidency

description: A suspected drug trafficker and former associate of the late Colombian drugs baron Pablo Escobar has been arrested at his luxury villa in the city of Medellin following an international operation, Spanish police said on Saturday.
title: Former Pablo Escobar associate arrested on drugs charges in Colombia

description: Greece’s parliament narrowly passed a bill early on Saturday that will allow foreign private universities to set up branches in the country, bucking weeks of protests by students who say the move will devalue degrees from public universities.
title: Greek parliament approves private foreign universities, bucking protests

description: Heavy gunfire was seen on Friday near Haiti's national palace in its capital of Port-au-Prince, according to reports by news agency EFE, in the midst of political turmoil sparked by Prime Minister Ariel Henry's absence.
title: Heavy gunfire near Haiti's National Palace in Port-au-Prince

description: Hungary's right-wing nationalist Prime Minister Viktor Orban lent his support to his long-time ally Donald Trump's bid to return to White House after meeting the former U.S. president in Florida late on Friday.
title: Hungary's PM Orban supports Trump after Florida meeting

description: Seven-year-old Safiya Kuriga complained she was feeling feverish but her mother still made her attend class on Thursday. Within two hours, gunmen entered her school and kidnapped Safiya and some 300 other students in Nigeria's northern Kaduna state.
title: 'I forced her to go to school', Nigerian mother cries after mass school abduction

description: India is expected to sign an economic agreement on Sunday with a group of four European countries aimed at increasing trade and investment, two officials with knowledge of the talks said, capping nearly 16 years of negotiations.
title: India, Europe trade group to sign pact on Sunday, sources say

description: Ireland looked set to reject proposals to replace constitutional references to the makeup of a family and women's "life within the home" when votes are counted on Saturday, in what would be a significant defeat for the government.
title: Ireland looks set to reject constitutional changes

description: Israel struck one of the largest residential towers in Rafah in the southern Gaza Strip on Saturday, residents said, stepping up pressure on the last area of the enclave it has not yet invaded and where over a million displaced Palestinians are sheltering.
title: Israel strikes landmark residential tower in southern Rafah as truce talks stall

description: Meghan, Britain's Duchess of Sussex, has said she was targeted with "hateful" online abuse during her two pregnancies, criticising the toxicity and lack of humanity on the internet and in parts of the media.
title: Meghan, Duchess of Sussex, hits out at 'hateful' abuse during pregnancies

description: Portugal's criminal police agency PJ said on Saturday it arrested a member of Italy's Camorra crime group who has been on the run for two decades.
title: Member of Italy's Camorra arrested in Portugal after 20 years on the run

description: Pakistan's former President Asif Ali Zardari won a second term on Saturday, supported by the ruling coalition in a vote by parliament and regional assemblies, the election presiding officer said.
title: Pakistan's former President Zardari wins another term

description: Poland's prime minister pledged to reduce a grain surplus on the domestic market at talks with farmers on Saturday, a government official said, but union leaders said they were pressing on with weeks of protests.
title: Polish government pledges grain surplus cut, farmers press on with protests

description: Pope Francis has accepted the resignation of a Polish bishop for negligence in handling cases of sexual abuse committed by some clergy against minors, his representatives in the country said on Saturday.
title: Pope accepts resignation of Polish bishop for negligence over abuse

description: Pope Francis has said in an interview that Ukraine should have what he called the courage of the "white flag" and negotiate an end to the war with Russia that followed Moscow's full-scale invasion two years ago and that has killed tens of thousands.
title: Pope says Ukraine should have 'courage of the white flag' of negotiations

description: Senegalese presidential candidates launched their shortened campaigns on Saturday, two days after a court confirmed the election would be held on March 24, ending weeks of uncertainty and kick-starting a competition that remains wide open.
title: Senegal kicks off short election campaign after poll delays

description: Sudan's Rapid Support Forces (RSF) paramilitary group on Saturday welcomed a call by the United Nations Security Council for a cessation of hostilities in the Muslim holy month of Ramadan, offering a potential respite from the 11-month-old conflict.
title: Sudan's RSF paramilitaries welcome UN call for cessation of hostilities in Ramadan

description: Thousands of Spaniards marched through the centre of Madrid on Saturday to protest against an amnesty bill for Catalan separatists involved in a failed 2017 independence bid.
title: Thousands march in Madrid to protest against Catalan amnesty law

description: Turkish and U.S. officials held comprehensive talks about the wars in Ukraine and Gaza and various bilateral issues during meetings in Washington, Turkey's foreign minister said late on Friday.
title: Turkey, US discuss Ukraine, Gaza, ways to improve ties, foreign minister says

description: Two more individuals linked to an independent Azerbaijani television station were arrested on Saturday and pleaded not guilty in court in connection with a probe into smuggling, one of their lawyers said.
title: Two more individuals arrested in move against Azerbaijan TV station

description: U.S. Navy ships and aircraft shot down 15 uncrewed aerial vehicle (UAVs) fired by Yemen's Houthis in the Red Sea area early on Saturday, U.S. Central Command (CENTCOM) said.
title: US Navy shoots down 15 UAVs in Red Sea area, CENTCOM says

description: Venezuela's attorney general on Saturday announced the arrest of a regional campaign leader for opposition leader Maria Corina Machado, citing alleged conspiracy, among other crimes.
title: Venezuela arrests close ally of opposition leader Machado

description: Yemen's Iran-aligned Houthis targeted bulk carrier Propel Fortune in the Gulf of Aden, the group's military spokesman Yahya Sarea said in a televised speech early on Saturday.
title: Yemen's Houthis say they targeted bulk carrier, number of US war destroyers in Red Sea
